docs.abstract: Amy Klobuchar has often spoken about her prosecution of the teenager in an 11-year-old girl’s murder. This week, an Associated Press report pointed to flaws in the case.
docs.snippet: Amy Klobuchar has often spoken about her prosecution of the teenager in an 11-year-old girl’s murder. This week, an Associated Press report pointed to flaws in the case.
docs.lead_paragraph: Civil rights activists and black community leaders in Minneapolis have called on Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota to suspend her presidential campaign after a report raised questions about whether a black teenager was wrongly convicted of murder during her tenure as the Hennepin County attorney.

headline.main: Klobuchar Faces Uproar Over Her Role in Black Teenager’s Murder Conviction
headline.print_headline: Klobuchar Faces Uproar for Role in Black Man’s Conviction

docs.abstract: The Los Angeles Police Commission voted last week to restore the badge of Robert William Stewart, one of the city’s first Black officers.
docs.snippet: The Los Angeles Police Commission voted last week to restore the badge of Robert William Stewart, one of the city’s first Black officers.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 1889, Robert William Stewart became one of the first Black police officers ever hired in California.

headline.main: A Black Police Officer Is Reinstated, 121 Years Later

docs.abstract: Racial justice and Ruth Bader Ginsburg’s legacy were also recurring themes during Sunday night’s ceremony.
docs.snippet: Racial justice and Ruth Bader Ginsburg’s legacy were also recurring themes during Sunday night’s ceremony.
docs.lead_paragraph: As vigils honoring Ruth Bader Ginsburg, the Supreme Court justice who died on Friday, continued throughout the United States on Sunday, television stars gathered virtually for the 72nd Primetime Emmy Awards, one of the first major awards shows to take place during the pandemic.

headline.main: This Year’s Emmy Winners Want You to Vote

docs.abstract: The judge upheld the more serious charge of second-degree murder against Derek Chauvin, the former Minneapolis police officer who was captured on video kneeling on Mr. Floyd’s neck.
docs.snippet: The judge upheld the more serious charge of second-degree murder against Derek Chauvin, the former Minneapolis police officer who was captured on video kneeling on Mr. Floyd’s neck.
docs.lead_paragraph: A judge has dropped a third-degree murder charge against Derek Chauvin, the former Minneapolis police officer accused of killing George Floyd on May 25 by kneeling on his neck for more than eight minutes.

headline.main: Judge Dismisses Third-Degree Murder Charge in George Floyd Killing

docs.abstract: The new editor said her predecessor, who wrote the incendiary editorial, was still interfering with the publication of The Democrat-Reporter.
docs.snippet: The new editor said her predecessor, who wrote the incendiary editorial, was still interfering with the publication of The Democrat-Reporter.
docs.lead_paragraph: When a white newspaper editor in Alabama drew widespread condemnation for an editorial that called for the Ku Klux Klan to ride again, only to be replaced by a black woman who hoped to take the newspaper in a new direction, it seemed like a symbolic moment.

headline.main: Black Editor Who Took Over Alabama Newspaper That Called for K.K.K. to ‘Ride Again’ Steps Down

docs.abstract: Some students in a mostly white New York suburb said the flag made them feel unsafe. Banning it prompted accusations of political bias.

docs.abstract: Since last summer, leaders of New York’s pre-eminent dance companies have been meeting weekly to share ideas and problems.
docs.snippet: Since last summer, leaders of New York’s pre-eminent dance companies have been meeting weekly to share ideas and problems.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last summer, Jonathan Stafford, the artistic director of New York City Ballet, was feeling isolated and anxious. It was a few months into the pandemic, and the strangeness of lockdown and the turmoil and urgency of the Black Lives Matter protests were on his mind.

headline.main: When Dance Shut Down, These Directors Banded Together
